summary:
The Security Council:
- Urges parties to sensitize populations about border demarcation and UN's role (para 9);
- Calls on parties to refrain from unilateral troop/population movements near the border (para 10);
- Reaffirms review of parties' progress in implementing Algiers Agreements (para 11);
- Encourages guarantors, facilitators, and witnesses to intensify contacts (para 12);
- Welcomes contributions to Trust Fund and calls for urgent further contributions (para 13);
- Calls on parties to increase efforts for confidence-building and normalization (para 14);
- Expresses concern at humanitarian situation and urges Member States to provide support (para 15);
- Invites African Union to continue supporting peace process (para 16);
- Expresses support for Special Representative, UNMEE personnel, and Boundary Commission (para 17);
- Decides to remain seized of the matter (para 18).
